                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17222697" author="lzljs3620320" created="Thu, 29 Oct 2020 04:09:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Now the filesystem wants to reuse serialization schema, but the behavior of each format is inconsistent. For example, the line separator is written in CSV, but JSON does not.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17222700" author="jark" created="Thu, 29 Oct 2020 04:16:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think &lt;tt&gt;csv.line-delimiter&lt;/tt&gt; is not a good option for csv format, the &lt;tt&gt;line-delimiter&lt;/tt&gt; should be an option of filesystem, because it is never used for message queues. &lt;br/&gt;
For the row-wise formats, it should consume and produce the bytes for a row. The line splitting should be handled by connectors. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I also searched the mailing list, and I didn&apos;t find any user asking questions about &lt;tt&gt;csv.line-delimiter&lt;/tt&gt;, only some people are asking &lt;tt&gt;csv.field-delimiter&lt;/tt&gt;. &lt;br/&gt;
Therefore, I think we can remove &lt;tt&gt;csv.line-delimiter&lt;/tt&gt; option (mention this in release note) and not append a new line in &lt;tt&gt;CsvRowDataSerializationSchema&lt;/tt&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What do you think?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17223397" author="liufangliang" created="Fri, 30 Oct 2020 03:51:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17227146" author="jark" created="Fri, 6 Nov 2020 03:30:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in master: 2d12d325d77e4727cb74d8a58597eb0ce9ab5aa2&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
